## AI Grand Challenge 2026 evaluation licence

For the purposes of the AI Grand Challenge 2026 (POTRAZ), the authors
grant POTRAZ and its designated adjudicators a non-exclusive,
royalty-free, revocable licence to:

  - evaluate this submission;
  - demonstrate this submission for public-interest purposes related to
    the Grand Challenge; and
  - pilot this submission with named participants, for the purposes of
    the Grand Challenge process.

This licence does not grant any right to redistribute, sublicense,
modify, or commercially exploit the software, in whole or in part,
outside of the evaluation, demonstration, and pilot activities described
above.

## Commercial use, procurement, and institutional adoption

Any use of this software beyond the Grand Challenge evaluation licence
above — including commercial use, government procurement, or
institutional adoption at production scale — requires a separate written
agreement with the authors.

## Third-party components

This software incorporates third-party open-source libraries under their
own licences (predominantly MIT, BSD, ISC, and Apache-2.0; no
copyleft/GPL-only dependency was found in a production-dependency audit
run 2026-07-11). See docs-vault-ready/06-grand-challenge-2026/
asset-and-licence-register.md in this repository for the full list and
how to reproduce the audit.
